  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "hi, `eth_call` can be executed query/tx in a specific block as this method shows\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/c503f98f6d5e80e079c1d8a3601d188af2a899da/ethclient/ethclient.go#L475\r\n\r\nis it possible to execute  `eth_call` in a specific block AND a specific index?\r\n\r\nI happened to see [this](http://tenderly.co) service, it can fork chain at a specific block and index, which is really cool!\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1725060/121190917-15bc9300-c89e-11eb-9c44-46dedd3d1adf.png)\r\n\r\nand then I can do simulation\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1725060/121190962-1c4b0a80-c89e-11eb-858d-2b68dfce530d.png)\r\n\r\nhow can I implement it in the native go-ethereum current codebase?",
